COSMOSformat

Class V3Component

  • java.lang.Object
    • COSMOSformat.COSMOScontentFormat
      • COSMOSformat.V3Component

  • public class V3Component
extends COSMOScontentFormat
    This class extends the COSMOScontentFormat base class to define a V3 record. It defines methods to parse the V3 data arrays, build a new V3 component from V3 processing results, and convert the V3 component into text for writing out to file.

    • Constructor Detail

      • V3Component

        public V3Component(java.lang.String procType)
        Use this constructor when the V3 component is read in from a file and filled in with the loadComponent method. In this case, there is no parentV2 associated with this V3.
        Parameters:
        procType - process level indicator (i.e. "V3")

      • V3Component

        public V3Component(java.lang.String procType,
                   V2Component pV2,
                   V2Component pV2vel,
                   V2Component pV2dis)
        Use this constructor when the V3 component is created from processing done on a V2 component. In this case, the contents of V3 are initialized to the V2 values and updated during the processing.
        Parameters:
        procType - process level indicator (i.e. "V3")
        pV2 - reference to the parent V2Component
        pV2vel - reference to the parent V2Component holding velocity
        pV2dis - reference to the parent V2Component holding displacement

      • buildV3

        public void buildV3(V3Process inVvals)
             throws SmException,
                    FormatException
        This method builds the V3 component from the V3 process object, picking up the data arrays and updating header parameters and format lines. Once in this method, the V3Process object is no longer needed and its array list is transferred to the V3Component object.
        Parameters:
        inVvals - the V3Process object
        Throws:
        SmException - if unable to access the header values
        FormatException - if unable to format the numeric values to text

      • buildNewDataFormatLine

        public java.lang.String buildNewDataFormatLine(java.lang.String units,
                                               int unitsCode,
                                               java.lang.String atype,
                                               java.lang.String stype,
                                               double damp)
        This method creates a new data format line for the V3 component data arrays.
        Parameters:
        units - the numeric code for the type of units, COSMOS table 2
        unitsCode - code containing the type of units (cm, cm/sec, etc.)
        atype - array type of "periods", "fft", or "spectra"
        stype - spectra type of "Sa", "Sv", or "Sd"
        damp - damping value
        Returns:
        the formatted data format line
